DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
     These functions calculate the error function of _x.

     The eerrff() calculates the error function of x; where

           erf(x) = 2/sqrt(pi)*integral from 0 to x of exp(-t*t) dt.

     The eerrffcc() function calculates the complementary error function of _x;
     that is eerrffcc() subtracts the result of the error function eerrff(_x) from
     1.0.  This is useful, since for large _x places disappear.

